  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\"/>\n<title>Suffix Tree (Trie + Compression) — Interactive Demo</title>\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"/>\n<style>\n  body { font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, \"Helvetica Neue\", Arial; margin: 0; padding: 0; display: flex; height: 100vh; }\n  #sidebar { width: 360px; min-width: 260px; max-width: 420px; padding: 16px; box-sizing: border-box; border-right: 1px solid #e0e0e0; background: #fafafa; overflow: auto; }\n  #main { flex: 1; display: flex; flex-direction: column; background: #fff; }\n  h1 { margin: 0 0 12px 0; font-size: 18px; }\n  label { display: block; margin-top: 8px; font-size: 13px; color: #333; }\n  input[type=\"text\"], textarea { width: 100%; padding: 8px; box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 14px; border: 1px solid #ccc; border-radius: 4px; }\n  .row { display: flex; gap: 8px; margin-top: 8px; }\n  button { padding: 8px 10px; background: #1976d2; color: white; border: none; border-radius: 4px; cursor: pointer; font-size: 14px; }\n  button.ghost { background: #e0e0e0; color: #111; }\n  small { color: #666; }\n  #info { margin-top: 12px; font-size: 13px; color: #444; line-height: 1.4; }\n  #suffixes { margin-top: 12px; max-height: 220px; overflow: auto; border-top: 1px dashed #ddd; padding-top: 8px; }\n  .sufItem { padding: 6px 8px; border-radius: 6px; cursor: pointer; margin-bottom: 6px; background: #fff; border: 1px solid #f0f0f0; }\n  .sufItem:hover { background: #f3f8ff; border-color: #d0e6ff; }\n  .sufItem.selected { background: #e6f0ff; border-color: #b6d1ff; }\n  #searchResult { margin-top: 8px; font-size: 13px; color: #333; }\n  #canvasWrap { flex: 1; position: relative; overflow: hidden; }\n  #svg { width: 100%; height: 100%; background: linear-gradient(180deg, #fff, #fbfbff); cursor: grab; }\n  .node { fill: #1976d2; stroke: #0e5ca8; stroke-width: 1; cursor: pointer; }\n  .leaf { fill: #43a047; stroke: #2e7d32; }\n  .nodeLabel { font-size: 12px; fill: #fff; pointer-events: none; dominant-baseline: middle; text-anchor: middle; }\n  .edge { stroke: #333; stroke-width: 1.2; fill: none; cursor: pointer; }\n  .edgeLabel { font-size: 12px; fill: #000; pointer-events: none; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); }\n  .highlightEdge { stroke: #ff6f00 !important; stroke-width: 3 !important; }\n  .highlightNode { stroke: #ff6f00 !important; stroke-width: 3 !important; }\n  .mini { font-size: 12px; color: #666; }\n  footer { padding: 8px 16px; font-size: 12px; color: #666; border-top: 1px solid #eee; background: #fafafa; }\n  /* tooltip */\n  .tip { position: absolute; background: rgba(0,0,0,0.8); color: #fff; padding: 6px 8px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 12px; pointer-events: none; display: none; z-index: 20; white-space: pre-wrap; }\n  .controlsGrid { display: grid; gap: 8px; grid-template-columns: 1fr auto; align-items: center; }\n  .muted { color: #888; font-size: 13px; }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<div id=\"sidebar\">\n  <h1>Suffix Tree — interactive demo</h1>\n  <label>Input string\n    <input id=\"inputStr\" type=\"text\" value=\"banana$\" />\n  </label>\n  <div class=\"row\">\n    <button id=\"buildBtn\">Build Tree</button>\n    <button id=\"randBtn\" class=\"ghost\">Random</button>\n    <button id=\"clearBtn\" class=\"ghost\">Clear</button>\n  </div>\n  <label style=\"margin-top:12px;\">Pattern search\n    <div class=\"controlsGrid\">\n      <input id=\"pattern\" type=\"text\" placeholder=\"Type a pattern to search (e.g., ana)\" />\n      <button id=\"searchBtn\">Search</button>\n    </div>\n  </label>\n  <div id=\"searchResult\" class=\"mini\">No search yet.</div>\n\n  <div id=\"info\">\n    This demo builds a suffix trie by inserting all suffixes, then compresses chains of single-child nodes into a suffix tree (a compact suffix tree). It lets you:\n    <ul>\n      <li>Click a suffix (left) to highlight its leaf in the tree.</li>\n      <li>Search a pattern to highlight the matched path and show matching suffix indices.</li>\n      <li>Drag to pan and use mouse wheel to zoom.</li>\n    </ul>\n    Tip: include a unique end marker (like $) to make all suffixes end at leaves.\n  </div>\n\n  <div id=\"suffixes\">\n    <div class=\"muted\">Suffixes (click to highlight)</div>\n    <div id=\"sufList\"></div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"margin-top:12px;\">\n    <div class=\"muted\">Notes</div>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Construction here is the simple \"insert all suffixes\" trie then compress (not Ukkonen's linear algorithm) — good for visualization.</li>\n      <li>Works best with strings up to ~150 characters in this demo.</li>\n    </ul>\n  </div>\n  <div style=\"height:14px\"></div>\n</div>\n\n<div id=\"main\">\n  <div id=\"canvasWrap\">\n    <svg id=\"svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 1600 900\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMinYMin meet\">\n      <defs>\n        <marker id=\"arrow\" markerWidth=\"6\" markerHeight=\"6\" refX=\"6\" refY=\"3\" orient=\"auto\">\n          <path d=\"M0,0 L6,3 L0,6 z\" fill=\"#333\" />\n        </marker>\n      </defs>\n      <g id=\"viewport\">\n        <!-- tree graphics go here -->\n      </g>\n    </svg>\n    <div id=\"tooltip\" class=\"tip\"></div>\n  </div>\n  <footer>\n    Visualization: nodes are circular, edges labeled with substrings. Leaves show suffix start index. Try \"banana$\" and search \"ana\".\n  </footer>\n</div>\n\n<script>\n(function(){\n  // Utilities\n  function escapeHtml(s){ return s.replace(/&/g,'&amp;').replace(/</g,'&lt;').replace(/>/g,'&gt;'); }\n  function $(id){ return document.getElementById(id); }\n\n  // Data structures: build suffix trie, then compress to tree\n  function buildSuffixTrie(s){\n    // Node: {children: Map<char, node>, parent, incoming: label (string), leafIndices: Set}\n    function newNode(){ return {children:new Map(), parent:null, incoming:'', leafIndices: new Set(), id: nextId++}; }\n    let root = newNode();\n    root.incoming = '';\n    let nextId = 0;\n    nextId = 1; // ensure root id 1?\n    root.id = 0;\n    for(let i=0;i<s.length;i++){\n      let cur = root;\n      cur.leafIndices.add(i);\n      for(let j=i;j<s.length;j++){\n        let ch = s[j];\n        if(!cur.children.has(ch)){\n          let nd = newNode();\n          nd.parent = cur;\n          nd.incoming = ch;\n          cur.children.set(ch, nd);\n        }\n        cur = cur.children.get(ch);\n        cur.leafIndices.add(i);\n      }\n    }\n    // assign ids\n    let idCount=1;\n    function walkAssign(n){\n      n.id = idCount++;\n      for(let c of n.children.values()) walkAssign(c);\n    }\n    walkAssign(root);\n    return root;\n  }\n\n  function compressTrie(root){\n    // Create new nodes and edges representing compressed tree.\n    // We'll perform DFS: whenever node has exactly one child, merge labels.\n    function compressNode(node){\n      let newNode = {children: [], parent:null, incoming: node.incoming, id: node.id, leafIndices: new Set(node.leafIndices)};\n      for(let [ch, child] of node.children){\n        let cur = child;\n        let label = cur.incoming;\n        // follow while single child\n        while(cur.children.size===1){\n          let [[nextCh, nextNode]] = cur.children.entries();\n          label += nextNode.incoming;\n          cur = nextNode;\n        }\n        // cur is the compressed-end child\n        let compressedChild = compressNode(cur);\n        compressedChild.incoming = label;\n        compressedChild.parent = newNode;\n        newNode.children.push(compressedChild);\n      }\n      return newNode;\n    }\n    // special: root.incoming='' but compressNode expects incoming on children; we pass root but ensure incoming kept\n    let compressedRoot = compressNode(root);\n    compressedRoot.incoming = '';\n    compressedRoot.parent = null;\n    return compressedRoot;\n  }\n\n  // Layout: simple tidy top-down layout based on leaf order\n  function layoutTree(root){\n    const levelHeight = 100;\n    // first compute leaves and assign x positions left-to-right\n    let xCounter = 50; // spacing\n    const xSpacing = 140;\n    function dfsAssign(node, depth){\n      node.depth = depth;\n      if(node.children.length===0){\n        node.x = xCounter;\n        xCounter += xSpacing;\n        node.y = depth * levelHeight + 50;\n      } else {\n        for(let ch of node.children) dfsAssign(ch, depth+1);\n        // set x center of children\n        let minX = Math.min(...node.children.map(c=>c.x));\n        let maxX = Math.max(...node.children.map(c=>c.x));\n        node.x = (minX + maxX)/2;\n        node.y = depth * levelHeight + 50;\n      }\n    }\n    dfsAssign(root, 0);\n  }\n\n  // Render into SVG\n  const svg = $('svg');\n  const viewport = $('viewport');\n  const tooltip = $('tooltip');\n\n  function clearSVG(){ while(viewport.firstChild) viewport.removeChild(viewport.firstChild); }\n\n  function renderTree(root, s){\n    clearSVG();\n    // draw edges then nodes; give each element a data-id\n    let edgesGroup = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg','g');\n    let nodesGroup = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg','g');\n    viewport.appendChild(edgesGroup);\n    viewport.appendChild(nodesGroup);\n\n    // traverse\n    function drawNode(node){\n      for(let child of node.children){\n        drawEdge(node, child);\n        drawNode(child);\n      }\n      drawCircle(node);\n    }\n\n    function drawEdge(parent, child){\n      // edge as path or line\n      let x1 = parent.x, y1 = parent.y;\n      let x2 = child.x, y2 = child.y;\n      // curve path for nicer look\n      let dx = 0;\n      let midY = (y1 + y2)/2;\n      let path = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg','path');\n      let d = `M ${x1} ${y1+12} C ${x1} ${midY} ${x2} ${midY} ${x2} ${y2-12}`;\n      path.setAttribute('d', d);\n      path.setAttribute('class', 'edge');\n      path.setAttribute('data-from', parent.id);\n      path.setAttribute('data-to', child.id);\n      path.setAttribute('data-label', child.incoming);\n      // marker optional: not necessary\n      path.addEventListener('mouseenter', (ev)=> showTipForEdge(ev, child));\n      path.addEventListener('mouseleave', hideTip);\n      path.addEventListener('click', (ev)=> { ev.stopPropagation(); selectEdge(path, child); });\n      edgesGroup.appendChild(path);\n\n      // label at midpoint of path (approx)\n      let midX = (x1 + x2)/2;\n      let midY2 = (y1 + y2)/2;\n      let txt = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg','text');\n      txt.setAttribute('x', midX);\n      txt.setAttribute('y', midY2);\n      txt.setAttribute('class','edgeLabel');\n      txt.setAttribute('text-anchor','middle');\n      txt.textContent = shortenLabel(child.incoming);\n      edgesGroup.appendChild(txt);\n\n      // hidden full-label tooltip via mouseover handled above\n    }\n\n    function shortenLabel(lbl){\n      if(lbl.length>18) return lbl.slice(0,8) + '…' + lbl.slice(-8);\n      return lbl;\n    }\n\n    function drawCircle(node){\n      let g = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg','g');\n      g.setAttribute('transform', `translate(${node.x},${node.y})`);\n      g.setAttribute('data-id', node.id);\n      let circle = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg','circle');\n      circle.setAttribute('r', 14);\n      circle.setAttribute('class', node.children.length===0 ? 'node leaf' : 'node');\n      circle.addEventListener('mouseenter', (ev)=> showTipForNode(ev, node));\n      circle.addEventListener('mouseleave', hideTip);\n      circle.addEventListener('click', (ev)=> { ev.stopPropagation(); selectNode(node); });\n      g.appendChild(circle);\n\n      // label: if leaf show indices\n      let label = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg','text');\n      label.setAttribute('class','nodeLabel');\n      label.textContent = node.children.length===0 ? Array.from(node.leafIndices).join(',') : '';\n      g.appendChild(label);\n\n      nodesGroup.appendChild(g);\n    }\n\n    drawNode(root);\n  }\n\n  // Tooltip helpers\n  function showTipForEdge(ev, child){\n    let text = `edge: \"${child.incoming}\"\\nleads to subtree with suffix indices:\\n${Array.from(child.leafIndices).join(', ')}`;\n    showTipAt(ev.clientX, ev.clientY, text);\n  }\n  function showTipForNode(ev, node){\n    let text = node.children.length===0 ?\n       `leaf node\\nsuffix starts at index(es): ${Array.from(node.leafIndices).join(', ')}` :\n       `internal node\\nsubtree suffix indices: ${Array.from(node.leafIndices).join(', ')}`;\n    showTipAt(ev.clientX, ev.clientY, text);\n  }\n  function showTipAt(x,y,text){\n    tooltip.style.left = (x + 12) + 'px';\n    tooltip.style.top = (y + 12) + 'px';\n    tooltip.textContent = text;\n    tooltip.style.display = 'block';\n  }\n  function hideTip(){ tooltip.style.display = 'none'; }\n\n  // Selection / highlighting\n  let lastHighlight = { edges: [], nodes: [] };\n  function clearHighlight(){\n    lastHighlight.edges.forEach(e=> e.classList.remove('highlightEdge'));\n    lastHighlight.nodes.forEach(n=> n.querySelector('circle')?.classList.remove('highlightNode'));\n    lastHighlight = { edges: [], nodes: [] };\n    // clear suffix selection list highlight\n    document.querySelectorAll('.sufItem').forEach(el => el.classList.remove('selected'));\n  }\n\n  function selectEdge(pathElem, childNode){\n    clearHighlight();\n    pathElem.classList.add('highlightEdge');\n    lastHighlight.edges.push(pathElem);\n    // highlight subtree nodes (leaves) of this child\n    highlightLeavesByIndices(Array.from(childNode.leafIndices));\n    showSearchResult(Array.from(childNode.leafIndices));\n  }\n\n  function selectNode(node){\n    clearHighlight();\n    // highlight path from root to node\n    let pathElems = [];\n    // Find edges along path: trace parents\n    let cur = node;\n    while(cur.parent){\n      let frm = cur.parent.id;\n      let to = cur.id;\n      // find path element\n      let selector = `path.edge[data-from=\"${frm}\"][data-to=\"${to}\"]`;\n      let pathElem = viewport.querySelector(selector);\n      if(pathElem){\n        pathElem.classList.add('highlightEdge');\n        lastHighlight.edges.push(pathElem);\n      }\n      cur = cur.parent;\n    }\n    // highlight node\n    let nodeGroup = viewport.querySelector(`g[data-id=\"${node.id}\"]`);\n    if(nodeGroup){\n      nodeGroup.querySelector('circle').classList.add('highlightNode');\n      lastHighlight.nodes.push(nodeGroup);\n    }\n    // highlight leaves under node\n    highlightLeavesByIndices(Array.from(node.leafIndices));\n    showSearchResult(Array.from(node.leafIndices));\n  }\n\n  function highlightLeavesByIndices(indices){\n    // find node groups for leaves with matching indices\n    document.querySelectorAll('g[data-id]').forEach(g=>{\n      let txt = g.querySelector('text');\n      if(!txt) return;\n      let ids = txt.textContent.split(',').filter(Boolean).map(x=>parseInt(x,10));\n      if(ids.length===0) return;\n      let matched = ids.some(id=> indices.includes(id));\n      if(matched){\n        g.querySelector('circle').classList.add('highlightNode');\n        lastHighlight.nodes.push(g);\n      }\n    });\n    // mark list items\n    document.querySelectorAll('.sufItem').forEach(el=>{\n      let id = parseInt(el.getAttribute('data-index'),10);\n      if(indices.includes(id)) el.classList.add('selected'); else el.classList.remove('selected');\n    });\n  }\n\n  function showSearchResult(indices){\n    let el = $('searchResult');\n    if(indices.length===0) el.textContent = 'No matches.';\n    else el.textContent = 'Matched suffix start indices: ' + indices.join(', ');\n  }\n\n  // Pattern search in compressed tree\n  function searchPattern(root, pattern){\n    // returns {matched: boolean, node: node (if ended exactly at node), edgeInfo: {parent, child, matchedOnLabelPrefixLength} (if ends inside edge), indices: []}\n    let cur = root;\n    let i = 0;\n    while(i < pattern.length){\n      let ch = pattern[i];\n      // find child whose incoming label starts with ch\n      let child = null;\n      for(let c of cur.children){\n        if(c.incoming[0] === ch){ child = c; break; }\n      }\n      if(!child) return {matched:false, indices: []};\n      // compare label with remaining pattern\n      let lbl = child.incoming;\n      let j=0;\n      while(j<lbl.length && i<pattern.length && lbl[j]===pattern[i]){ j++; i++; }\n      if(i===pattern.length){\n        // matched ends inside this label (possibly exactly at end)\n        // gather indices from child subtree\n        return {matched:true, node: null, edgeInfo:{parent:cur, child:child, matchedOnLabelPrefixLength:j}, indices: Array.from(child.leafIndices)};\n      }\n      if(j<lbl.length && i<pattern.length){\n        // mismatch inside label\n        return {matched:false, indices: []};\n      }\n      // j==lbl.length -> move down\n      cur = child;\n    }\n    // matched entire pattern exactly at cur (either root or internal node)\n    return {matched:true, node: cur, edgeInfo:null, indices: Array.from(cur.leafIndices)};\n  }\n\n  // Controls and glue\n  let currentCompressed = null;\n  let currentString = '';\n\n  function buildAndRender(){\n    let s = $('inputStr').value;\n    if(!s || s.length===0){ alert('Please enter a string.'); return; }\n    currentString = s;\n    // build\n    let trieRoot = buildSuffixTrie(s);\n    let compressed = compressTrie(trieRoot);\n    // copy leafIndices up property: compress already assigned\n    layoutTree(compressed);\n    renderTree(compressed, s);\n    currentCompressed = compressed;\n    populateSuffixList(s);\n    clearHighlight();\n    $('searchResult').textContent = 'Built suffix tree for string of length ' + s.length + '.';\n  }\n\n  function populateSuffixList(s){\n    let list = $('sufList');\n    list.innerHTML = '';\n    for(let i=0;i<s.length;i++){\n      let div = document.createElement('div');\n      div.className = 'sufItem';\n      div.setAttribute('data-index', i);\n      div.textContent = `${i}: ${s.slice(i)}`;\n      div.addEventListener('click', ()=> {\n        // find leaf node(s) that contain this index\n        clearHighlight();\n        // find any g containing this index\n        document.querySelectorAll('g[data-id]').forEach(g=>{\n          let txt = g.querySelector('text');\n          if(!txt) return;\n          let ids = txt.textContent.split(',').filter(Boolean).map(x=>parseInt(x,10));\n          if(ids.includes(i)){\n            // highlight path to this node: find node group\n            let gid = g.getAttribute('data-id');\n            // find node in our compressed tree structure by id\n            let target = findNodeById(currentCompressed, parseInt(gid,10));\n            if(target) selectNode(target);\n            // highlight list item\n            document.querySelectorAll('.sufItem').forEach(el => el.classList.remove('selected'));\n            div.classList.add('selected');\n          }\n        });\n      });\n      list.appendChild(div);\n    }\n  }\n\n  function findNodeById(root, id){\n    if(!root) return null;\n    if(root.id === id) return root;\n    for(let c of root.children){\n      let r = findNodeById(c, id);\n      if(r) return r;\n    }\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  // pattern search UI\n  $('searchBtn').addEventListener('click', ()=> {\n    let pat = $('pattern').value;\n    if(!currentCompressed){ alert('Build a tree first.'); return; }\n    if(!pat || pat.length===0){ alert('Type a pattern.'); return; }\n    clearHighlight();\n    let res = searchPattern(currentCompressed, pat);\n    if(!res.matched){\n      $('searchResult').textContent = 'No match found.';\n      return;\n    }\n    // highlight path: if matched ended inside edge, highlight that edge and the matched portion by highlighting the whole edge\n    if(res.edgeInfo){\n      // find path element\n      let parent = res.edgeInfo.parent;\n      let child = res.edgeInfo.child;\n      let pathElem = viewport.querySelector(`path.edge[data-from=\"${parent.id}\"][data-to=\"${child.id}\"]`);\n      if(pathElem){\n        pathElem.classList.add('highlightEdge');\n        lastHighlight.edges.push(pathElem);\n      }\n      // highlight subtree leaves under child\n      highlightLeavesByIndices(res.indices);\n      showSearchResult(res.indices);\n    } else if(res.node){\n      selectNode(res.node);\n    } else {\n      $('searchResult').textContent = 'Matched (no node/edge?)';\n    }\n  });\n\n  // build button\n  $('buildBtn').addEventListener('click', buildAndRender);\n  $('randBtn').addEventListener('click', ()=> {\n    // generate random lowercase string with $\n    let n = 8 + Math.floor(Math.random()*8);\n    let arr = [];\n    let alph = 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz';\n    for(let i=0;i<n-1;i++) arr.push(alph.charAt(Math.floor(Math.random()*alph.length)));\n    arr.push('$');\n    $('inputStr').value = arr.join('');\n  });\n  $('clearBtn').addEventListener('click', ()=> {\n    $('inputStr').value = '';\n    $('pattern').value = '';\n    clearHighlight();\n    currentCompressed = null;\n    $('sufList').innerHTML = '';\n    $('searchResult').textContent = 'Cleared.';\n    clearSVG();\n  });\n\n  // initial build\n  buildAndRender();\n\n  // Pan & zoom for svg\n  (function(){\n    let svgEl = svg;\n    let vp = viewport;\n    let state = {dragging:false, lastX:0, lastY:0, tx:0, ty:0, scale:1};\n    // initial transform\n    vp.setAttribute('transform','translate(0,0) scale(1)');\n    svgEl.addEventListener('mousedown', (e)=>{\n      state.dragging = true;\n      state.lastX = e.clientX; state.lastY = e.clientY;\n      svgEl.style.cursor = 'grabbing';\n    });\n    window.addEventListener('mousemove', (e)=>{\n      if(!state.dragging) return;\n      let dx = e.clientX - state.lastX;\n      let dy = e.clientY - state.lastY;\n      state.lastX = e.clientX; state.lastY = e.clientY;\n      state.tx += dx; state.ty += dy;\n      updateTransform();\n    });\n    window.addEventListener('mouseup', (e)=>{\n      state.dragging = false; svgEl.style.cursor = 'grab';\n    });\n    function updateTransform(){\n      vp.setAttribute('transform', `translate(${state.tx} ${state.ty}) scale(${state.scale})`);\n    }\n    svgEl.addEventListener('wheel', (e)=>{\n      e.preventDefault();\n      // zoom relative to pointer\n      const scaleFactor = 1.08;\n      let pt = getSvgPoint(e.clientX, e.clientY);\n      let beforeX = (pt.x - state.tx) / state.scale;\n      let beforeY = (pt.y - state.ty) / state.scale;\n      if(e.deltaY < 0) state.scale *= scaleFactor; else state.scale /= scaleFactor;\n      // clamp\n      state.scale = Math.max(0.2, Math.min(5, state.scale));\n      // after adjusting scale, compute new tx/ty so that pointer keeps same world coords\n      let afterX = beforeX * state.scale + state.tx;\n      let afterY = beforeY * state.scale + state.ty;\n      state.tx += (pt.x - afterX);\n      state.ty += (pt.y - afterY);\n      updateTransform();\n    }, {passive:false});\n\n    function getSvgPoint(clientX, clientY){\n      let pt = svgEl.createSVGPoint();\n      pt.x = clientX; pt.y = clientY;\n      let ctm = svgEl.getScreenCTM();\n      if(ctm) return pt.matrixTransform(ctm.inverse());\n      return {x: clientX, y: clientY};\n    }\n  })();\n\n  // click background to clear highlight\n  svg.addEventListener('click', ()=> clearHighlight());\n\n  // expose in window for debugging\n  window._st_demo = { buildAndRender, searchPattern, currentCompressed };\n})();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
